<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-822-530  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 822 530.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Sept 6 1990 n1506* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Unveils fibre optic links, Sysplex master clock.... (new IBMproducts) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionFiber OpticsClocksMultiprocessingCommunications EquipmentWide Area NetworksMainframe Computers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>UNVEILS FIBRE OPTIC LINKS, SYSPLEX MASTER CLOCK...andM;One of the more important innovations in System/390 is Enterprise SystemsConnection Architecture or Escon, those long-awaited fibre optic channels,which enables installations to be dispersed over a radius of five and a halfmiles.andP;  The channels, which are optional, run at up to 10Mbytes-per-secondusing a new proprietary protocol.andP;  IBM characterises Esco as the first majoradvance in channel architecture since the System/360 in 1964, and it isaccompanied by an Escon Director, which enables channel-to-control-unit orchannel-to-channel connections to be dynamically switched among severalpaths.andP;  The Escon channels are supported on all ES/9000 processors.andP;  Theother major new facility is multisystem coupling, or sysplex, where theclocks of up to eight machines can be synchronised to a master clock, whichmeans that up to eight six processor machines can be run as a loosely-coupledcomplex - that's a lot of MIPS.andP;  A companion console consolidation featureenables simplified operation of such a system complex: these features aresupported only in MVS/ESA SP Version 4.2, due sometime next year.andP;  WithinMVS/ESA SP 4 is a new APPC/MVS with SAA CPI Communications support to provideLU6.2 communications with other LU 6.2 devices such as OS/2 machines.andP;  Thenew version also provides for dynamic changes to the processor'schannel-attached input-output configuration definition so that the user canadd, delete, or modify a hardware and software input-output configurationdefinition without shutting the machine down.andP;  The ES/9000 water-cooledmodels implement a new Integrated Cryptographic Feature that enables users tostore, transmit, and manipulate data with the knowledge that the content ofthe data is secure from external access in any form other than encrypted.andO;The new ES/9000 processors support the functions of ESA/390 architecture andSystem/370 architecture is supported only in a logical partition.andP;  NewES/3090-9000T transition models and some 3090 J-Models support ESA/370architecture and parts of ESA/390 architecture.andO;</TEXT></DOC>